article.headline: Rutgers 75, South Carolina State 68
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Marquis Webb scored a career-high 28 points to lead Rutgers to a 75-68 win over South Carolina State Sunday. The Knights (7-6) made good use of the return of J.R. Inman and Anthony Farmer, who had sat out last week's loss at North Carolina due to academic reasons. The sophomores combined for 30 points to help overmatch the Bulldogs (3-8). Farmer had 16 points, five assists and six rebounds, and Inman almost reached a double-double with 15 points and nine rebounds. Webb was 8-for-14 from the field including 5-of-8 from 3-point range to shatter his former career high of 19 points. He added six rebounds and three assists. South Carolina State played without leading scorer Travis Jones, who didn't make the trip due to a knee injury. Derrick Davis led the Bulldogs with 23 points. After going up by 17 points in the second half, the Knights saw their lead dwindle to four points with only 18 seconds remaining on a 3-pointer by Davis. Webb went 6-for-6 from the line in the final minute and change to help wrap up the victory for Rutgers. Rutgers has won six of its last seven games and heads into the Big East schedule with a winning record after starting the season 1-5.
